                  </hi>. I am foreman to the prosecutor; the prisoner lived with him. On the 2nd of August he returned home, about three o'clock in the afternoon—Mrs. Dobson was booking my bread, and told him she would book his bread when she had done mine—he made no an<lb></lb>swer, but went out of the shop and did not return.</p>
